WEBVTT

STYLE
::cue(c.color9CD5FF) { color: #9CD5FF; }
::cue(c.colora8c7fa) { color: #a8c7fa; }

1
00:00:01.000 --> 00:00:07.000 line:5% align:middle
<b><c.color9CD5FF>One Pace Premium</c></b>
Keep the project alive: <c.colora8c7fa>ko-fi.com/not6ip</c>

2
00:00:00.980 --> 00:00:05.150
[dramatic orchestral music]

3
00:00:01.610 --> 00:00:02.610
[NARRATOR]
Wealth...

4
00:00:02.610 --> 00:00:03.820
[NARRATOR]
Wealth... Fame...

5
00:00:03.820 --> 00:00:05.150
[NARRATOR]
Wealth... Fame... Power...

6
00:00:05.150 --> 00:00:07.860
Gold Roger, the King of the Pirates,

7
00:00:07.860 --> 00:00:12.240
attained this and everything else
the world had to offer.

8
00:00:12.240 --> 00:00:17.370
And his dying words drove
countless souls to the seas.

9
00:00:17.910 --> 00:00:19.500
[GOLD ROGER]
You want my treasure?

10
00:00:19.500 --> 00:00:20.670
You can have it!

11
00:00:20.670 --> 00:00:24.170
I left everything I gathered
together in one place.

12
00:00:24.170 --> 00:00:26.340
Now you just have to find it!

13
00:00:26.340 --> 00:00:29.380
[NARRATOR]
These words lured men to the Grand Line

14
00:00:29.380 --> 00:00:33.010
in pursuit of dreams greater than
they'd ever dared to imagine!

15
00:00:33.010 --> 00:00:36.640
This is the time known as the Great Pirate Era!

16
00:00:36.640 --> 00:00:39.310
[whimsical orchestral music]

17
00:00:37.930 --> 00:00:42.180
The Dawn of an Adventure

18
00:00:39.310 --> 00:00:42.190
[NARRATOR]
This is a small seaport village.

19
00:00:42.190 --> 00:00:46.190
For the past year or so, a pirate ship
has been anchored at the port.

20
00:00:46.190 --> 00:00:51.660
A soft wind from the east blows gently
over this peaceful, sleepy place.

21
00:00:51.660 --> 00:00:54.740
[SHANKS]
Luffy! Come on!
What are you doing up there?

22
00:00:54.200 --> 00:00:54.740
[LUFFY]
Hmph!

23
00:00:55.370 --> 00:00:56.790
[growls]

24
00:00:56.570 --> 00:01:02.040
Monkey D. Luffy
Village Boy

25
00:00:56.790 --> 00:00:58.910
I'm not kiddin' around, do you hear me?!

26
00:00:58.910 --> 00:01:00.290
I'm really mad!

27
00:01:00.290 --> 00:01:02.040
Watch, I'll prove it to ya!

28
00:01:02.420 --> 00:01:05.340
[SHANKS laughs]
Yeah, go ahead, kid!

29
00:01:05.340 --> 00:01:07.880
Not sure what you're planning to do, though.

30
00:01:09.590 --> 00:01:10.800
[RED HAIR PIRATES scream]

31
00:01:10.800 --> 00:01:11.930
[LUFFY]
Ow!

32
00:01:11.930 --> 00:01:14.390
[SHANKS]
You idiot, what'd you do that for?!

33
00:01:14.890 --> 00:01:15.930
All right, drink up!

34
00:01:15.930 --> 00:01:17.390
[RED HAIR PIRATES cheering]

35
00:01:16.970 --> 00:01:22.560
[ragtime piano music]

36
00:01:17.390 --> 00:01:20.810
[RED HAIR PIRATE]
Let's drink to Luffy's courage
and our great journey on the sea!

37
00:01:20.810 --> 00:01:22.560
Cheers!

38
00:01:23.400 --> 00:01:25.440
Ha. Didn't hurt at all!

39
00:01:25.440 --> 00:01:27.730
[SHANKS]
That's a lie if I've ever heard one.

40
00:01:27.730 --> 00:01:28.940
I'm not lying!

41
00:01:28.940 --> 00:01:31.780
And I'm not scared of gettin' hurt again, either!

42
00:01:31.780 --> 00:01:34.160
You gotta take me with you
on your next voyage!

43
00:01:34.160 --> 00:01:35.950
I wanna be a pirate like you!

44
00:01:35.950 --> 00:01:39.950
[laughs] Yeah, right, as if
you could ever be a pirate!

45
00:01:40.200 --> 00:01:43.580
"Red-Haired" Shanks
Pirate Captain

46
00:01:40.330 --> 00:01:43.580
I don't think you're gonna fare
too well at sea if you sink like an anchor!

47
00:01:43.580 --> 00:01:46.380
I'll be okay as long as I don't fall overboard!

48
00:01:46.380 --> 00:01:48.710
And besides, I'm a really good fighter, too!

49
00:01:49.090 --> 00:01:50.510
I've got lots of training!

50
00:01:50.510 --> 00:01:53.470
I mean, when I punch people,
it's like firin' a pistol!

51
00:01:53.470 --> 00:01:56.180
A pistol? If you say so.

52
00:01:56.180 --> 00:01:57.810
Are you makin' fun of me?!

53
00:01:57.810 --> 00:01:59.180
[RED HAIR PIRATE]
Luffy!

54
00:01:59.560 --> 00:02:01.640
Don't be in such a sour mood, kiddo!

55
00:02:01.640 --> 00:02:04.150
You're still young, you should be having fun!

56
00:02:04.150 --> 00:02:07.020
And being a pirate's more fun than anything!

57
00:02:07.020 --> 00:02:09.280
We get to travel across the endless sea.

58
00:02:09.280 --> 00:02:11.690
Discoverin' new places all the time!

59
00:02:11.690 --> 00:02:13.200
We're as free as can be!

60
00:02:14.660 --> 00:02:17.990
I'd appreciate it if you clowns
didn't teach him that kind of thing.

61
00:02:17.990 --> 00:02:20.040
But you know it's true, right?

62
00:02:20.040 --> 00:02:23.670
Come on, Boss, we can take him on
one little voyage. What's the harm?

63
00:02:23.670 --> 00:02:25.500
[RED HAIR PIRATE]
Yeah, he'll be okay!

64
00:02:25.500 --> 00:02:28.250
[SHANKS]
Fine, but one of you gets left behind.

65
00:02:28.250 --> 00:02:31.380
[ROUX]
Yeah, forget that! Let's get back to drinkin'!

66
00:02:31.380 --> 00:02:32.970
[LUFFY]
Weren't you guys on my side?!

67
00:02:32.970 --> 00:02:36.050
I'm just sayin', you're much too young
to try and strike out to sea.

68
00:02:36.050 --> 00:02:38.930
You can ask me about it in ten years,
 and maybe I'll reconsider.

69
00:02:38.930 --> 00:02:41.680
Stupid Shanks! I'm not that little!

70
00:02:41.680 --> 00:02:44.440
Geez. Calm down. Drink some juice, kid.

71
00:02:44.440 --> 00:02:47.560
Ha! Yay, thank you! Ha!

72
00:02:47.560 --> 00:02:49.730
Real pirates don't drink juice, big guy!

73
00:02:49.730 --> 00:02:51.480
[LUFFY]
No, that's not fair, you tricked me!

74
00:02:51.480 --> 00:02:54.650
[LUFFY groans]
Whatever, I'm tired now!

75
00:02:54.650 --> 00:02:55.530
[BECKMAN]
Luffy.

76
00:02:55.530 --> 00:02:57.910
You have to try to understand
how the boss feels.

77
00:02:57.910 --> 00:02:58.870
Mr. First Mate!

78
00:02:59.830 --> 00:03:03.330
Think about it. This guy is the captain
of a tough-as-nails pirate crew.

79
00:03:03.330 --> 00:03:07.250
So he knows more than anybody how
dangerous this kind of life can be.

80
00:03:07.250 --> 00:03:10.130
My point is, he told you
not to come along with us

81
00:03:10.130 --> 00:03:11.800
because he didn't want to break your spirit.

82
00:03:12.050 --> 00:03:13.210
You don't get it!

83
00:03:13.210 --> 00:03:16.590
He's just makin' fun of me
'cause he thinks I'm a kid!

84
00:03:16.590 --> 00:03:17.720
Hey, Anchor!

85
00:03:17.720 --> 00:03:18.510
[LUFFY]
You see?!

86
00:03:18.930 --> 00:03:20.930
You're having fun as always.

87
00:03:20.930 --> 00:03:23.680
Yeah. I get such a kick out of
giving this kid a hard time.

88
00:03:24.640 --> 00:03:27.270
Luffy, would you like to order
some food, too?

89
00:03:27.270 --> 00:03:28.100
Mm-hmm!

90
00:03:28.100 --> 00:03:29.860
Put it on my treasure tab, 'kay?

91
00:03:29.860 --> 00:03:31.650
The treasure tab again?

92
00:03:31.650 --> 00:03:33.900
You know that does qualify as stealing.

93
00:03:33.900 --> 00:03:34.780
Nuh-uh!

94
00:03:34.780 --> 00:03:37.030
Once I become a pirate
and find a bunch of treasure,

95
00:03:37.030 --> 00:03:38.530
I'm gonna pay back every last bit!

96
00:03:38.530 --> 00:03:39.370
[MAKINO giggles]

97
00:03:39.370 --> 00:03:40.990
I know you will.

98
00:03:40.990 --> 00:03:42.290
[LUFFY giggles]

99
00:03:42.910 --> 00:03:43.830
[LUFFY]
Shanks!

100
00:03:43.830 --> 00:03:45.000
[SHANKS]
Yeah. What?

101
00:03:45.000 --> 00:03:47.250
[LUFFY]
How much longer are you gonna be here for?

102
00:03:47.250 --> 00:03:50.130
I'm not too sure. I believe
the plan we decided on

103
00:03:50.130 --> 00:03:51.750
was to go on a couple more voyages

104
00:03:51.750 --> 00:03:54.590
then head out towards the north
after we're done with that.

105
00:03:54.590 --> 00:03:55.420
[LUFFY]
Hmm...

106
00:03:56.260 --> 00:03:58.220
Only a couple more trips, huh?

107
00:03:58.970 --> 00:03:59.510
[MAKINO]
Huh?

108
00:04:01.050 --> 00:04:04.060
Okay, then I can practice
my swimming while you're here!

109
00:04:04.060 --> 00:04:06.850
[SHANKS]
That's a good idea. Knock yourself out.

110
00:04:09.400 --> 00:04:11.730
[tense orchestral music]

111
00:04:11.730 --> 00:04:13.400
[HIGUMA]
Excuse us.

112
00:04:13.400 --> 00:04:15.990
So these are what pass for pirates here?

113
00:04:15.990 --> 00:04:17.950
Looks awfully sad to me.

114
00:04:21.030 --> 00:04:25.200
[footsteps continue]

115
00:04:27.160 --> 00:04:29.330
You see, we're mountain bandits.

116
00:04:29.330 --> 00:04:32.340
But... we didn't come here
to tear your place apart.

117
00:04:32.340 --> 00:04:33.840
We'll just take some booze.

118
00:04:33.840 --> 00:04:35.760
[nervously] I'm so sorry, sir, but we're actually

119
00:04:35.760 --> 00:04:37.470
fresh out of alcohol for the moment.

120
00:04:37.470 --> 00:04:40.970
[HIGUMA]
Huh? Those pirates seem
to be drinking, though.

121
00:04:41.390 --> 00:04:42.720
Is that water?

122
00:04:42.720 --> 00:04:46.180
[MAKINO]
No, that was the last bit
of what I had stocked up.

123
00:04:46.180 --> 00:04:48.350
Well, this is a problem, isn't it?

124
00:04:48.350 --> 00:04:53.150
It looks like my friends and I drank the place
dry before you gentlemen came in. Sorry.

125
00:04:53.150 --> 00:04:53.820
[HIGUMA]
Huh?

126
00:04:53.820 --> 00:04:55.570
You can have this one if you like.

127
00:04:55.570 --> 00:04:57.400
It hasn't even been opened yet.

128
00:04:57.400 --> 00:04:58.570
Hm...

129
00:05:00.660 --> 00:05:01.450
[MAKINO gasps]

130
00:05:03.990 --> 00:05:05.790
[menacing music]
[dripping]

131
00:05:05.790 --> 00:05:07.370
[HIGUMA]
How dare you.

132
00:05:07.370 --> 00:05:09.910
Can you not see who you're talking to?

133
00:05:09.910 --> 00:05:13.250
You know damn well that won't
even be enough for a nightcap.

134
00:05:13.250 --> 00:05:14.920
Aww...

135
00:05:14.920 --> 00:05:16.800
Now the floor's all wet and sticky.

136
00:05:16.800 --> 00:05:18.090
Look at this, pal.

137
00:05:18.090 --> 00:05:20.930
I've got a bounty of
eight million berries on my head.

138
00:05:21.630 --> 00:05:26.260
I've killed fifty-six people, and all of 'em
were mouthy fools like you.

139
00:05:26.260 --> 00:05:28.560
If I were you, I'd watch my back.

140
00:05:28.560 --> 00:05:32.810
But since we're in the mountains and you're
on the sea, maybe we won't meet again.

141
00:05:33.440 --> 00:05:33.770
Huh?

142
00:05:34.810 --> 00:05:36.980
Sorry about the mess, Makino.

143
00:05:36.980 --> 00:05:38.480
Have you got a rag?

144
00:05:38.480 --> 00:05:41.150
[MAKINO]
Oh, no, don't worry, I can take care of it.

145
00:05:48.660 --> 00:05:50.660
Since you like to clean so much,

146
00:05:50.660 --> 00:05:53.500
I think you might find
this mess more fulfilling.

147
00:05:53.500 --> 00:05:54.670
[BANDITS chuckle]

148
00:05:56.170 --> 00:05:57.130
[HIGUMA chuckles]

149
00:05:59.550 --> 00:06:02.340
[BANDITS chuckling]

150
00:06:04.180 --> 00:06:06.600
Guess I'll see you weaklings another day.

151
00:06:06.600 --> 00:06:08.930
[HIGUMA laughs]

152
00:06:12.140 --> 00:06:13.520
[MAKINO footsteps]

153
00:06:13.520 --> 00:06:15.480
Are you all right, Captain Shanks?

154
00:06:15.480 --> 00:06:17.270
[SHANKS]
Never been better, Makino.

155
00:06:18.360 --> 00:06:19.280
[chuckles]

156
00:06:19.860 --> 00:06:21.070
[PIRATES laughing]

157
00:06:21.070 --> 00:06:23.070
[ROUX]
That fella really got you good!

158
00:06:23.070 --> 00:06:24.990
[YASOPP]
Talk about a loser!

159
00:06:24.990 --> 00:06:26.950
[laughing]

160
00:06:26.950 --> 00:06:28.740
[LUFFY]
Why are you laughing?!

161
00:06:28.740 --> 00:06:29.490
[MAKINO, SHANKS]
Huh?

162
00:06:29.490 --> 00:06:31.540
You should've stood up to him, Shanks!

163
00:06:31.540 --> 00:06:33.540
That wasn't cool at all!

164
00:06:33.540 --> 00:06:38.540
If you can laugh over something like that,
then you're not a man, or a real pirate!

165
00:06:39.500 --> 00:06:42.050
Look, Luffy, I know how you feel, kid.

166
00:06:42.050 --> 00:06:44.680
But all the guy did was
spill a little booze on me.

167
00:06:44.680 --> 00:06:46.930
It's not worth getting so upset about.

168
00:06:46.930 --> 00:06:49.180
[LUFFY growls]

169
00:06:49.180 --> 00:06:51.020
[SHANKS]
Hey, wait a second.

170
00:06:51.020 --> 00:06:53.480
Leave me alone. You're just a coward!

171
00:06:54.270 --> 00:06:54.980
[SHANKS]
Hm?

172
00:06:55.650 --> 00:06:56.190
[LUFFY]
Hm?

173
00:06:59.820 --> 00:07:00.360
[RED HAIR PIRATES scream]

174
00:07:00.360 --> 00:07:01.860
[rousing music]
Why's he stretchy?

175
00:07:01.860 --> 00:07:03.530
Oh no, don't tell me...!

176
00:07:03.530 --> 00:07:05.110
What the heck?!

177
00:07:05.110 --> 00:07:05.910
[shocked] It's gone!

178
00:07:05.910 --> 00:07:07.030
[RED HAIR PIRATES]
No way!

179
00:07:07.030 --> 00:07:09.620
Yeah, the Gum-Gum Fruit we looted!
It was right in here!

180
00:07:10.240 --> 00:07:11.450
Luffy, tell the truth.

181
00:07:11.450 --> 00:07:13.500
Did you just eat something like this?!

182
00:07:13.500 --> 00:07:16.370
[LUFFY]
Uh, yeah. It tasted gross though.

183
00:07:16.370 --> 00:07:17.790
[SHANKS]
What have you done?!

184
00:07:17.790 --> 00:07:20.800
The Gum-Gum Fruit is one of
the legendary devil fruits!

185
00:07:20.800 --> 00:07:22.670
It makes your body turn into rubber.

186
00:07:22.670 --> 00:07:25.760
This means that you've lost the ability
to swim for the rest of your life!

187
00:07:25.760 --> 00:07:28.260
Huh?! That can't be!

188
00:07:28.260 --> 00:07:31.430
You idiot!

189
00:07:34.390 --> 00:07:36.730
Hey, fish guy! Can I have a fishy?

190
00:07:36.730 --> 00:07:38.060
Luffy, it's you!

191
00:07:38.060 --> 00:07:41.400
I heard you missed out on another
big adventure with the pirates.

192
00:07:41.400 --> 00:07:42.360
That's okay!

193
00:07:42.360 --> 00:07:44.360
My body's made outta rubber now.

194
00:07:44.360 --> 00:07:48.700
This is more fun than goin'
on a voyage anyway! See?

195
00:07:48.700 --> 00:07:49.700
[LUFFY chuckles]

196
00:07:50.870 --> 00:07:53.080
The crew's been out at sea for a long time,

197
00:07:53.080 --> 00:07:54.250
isn't that right, Luffy?

198
00:07:54.790 --> 00:07:56.290
I bet you miss them.

199
00:07:56.290 --> 00:07:59.130
No way! I'm still upset with those guys.

200
00:07:59.130 --> 00:08:01.460
I thought Shanks and his crew
were cool pirates,

201
00:08:01.460 --> 00:08:03.170
but it turns out they're all totally wimpy!

202
00:08:03.170 --> 00:08:04.460
I don't know.

203
00:08:04.460 --> 00:08:06.970
I think being able to laugh
after somebody humiliates you

204
00:08:06.970 --> 00:08:08.970
like those bandits did is cool, too.

205
00:08:08.970 --> 00:08:11.010
You don't understand, Makino.

206
00:08:11.010 --> 00:08:13.760
Sometimes a man's gotta stand up and fight!

207
00:08:13.760 --> 00:08:15.730
You're right, maybe I don't get it, huh?

208
00:08:15.730 --> 00:08:17.890
[HIGUMA]
We're back for more.

209
00:08:17.890 --> 00:08:18.770
[BOTH]
Huh?

210
00:08:18.770 --> 00:08:21.560
[forboding orchestral music]
Looks like those damn pirates
aren't here today.

211
00:08:21.560 --> 00:08:24.690
We were in the neighborhood,
so we thought we'd stop in for a drink.

212
00:08:24.690 --> 00:08:27.860
[BANDITS chuckling]

213
00:08:28.240 --> 00:08:29.070
[gasps]

214
00:08:30.410 --> 00:08:32.030
What's the holdup, honey?

215
00:08:32.030 --> 00:08:33.740
Bring the booze!

216
00:08:35.620 --> 00:08:37.290
[worried gasps]

217
00:08:37.290 --> 00:08:38.620
[MAKINO]
Mayor, please help!

218
00:08:38.620 --> 00:08:40.420
What's the matter, Makino?

219
00:08:40.420 --> 00:08:43.250
It's Luffy! He's in big trouble!

220
00:08:43.250 --> 00:08:44.300
[BANDITS chuckling]

221
00:08:44.300 --> 00:08:46.710
[LUFFY]
Let go of me or else, you sick monster!

222
00:08:45.100 --> 00:08:46.710
[HIGUMA]
Well, this is interesting!

223
00:08:46.710 --> 00:08:48.840
[grunting]

224
00:08:48.840 --> 00:08:50.010
You're gonna pay for that!

225
00:08:50.010 --> 00:08:52.300
This kid is a freak of nature.

226
00:08:52.890 --> 00:08:54.060
[HIGUMA laughs]

227
00:08:54.060 --> 00:08:56.520
[BANDITS laughing]

228
00:08:56.520 --> 00:08:58.600
Say you're sorry for last time, right now!

229
00:08:58.600 --> 00:09:01.650
Wonder how much money we could
get if we sold him off?

230
00:09:02.270 --> 00:09:03.900
[yelling]

231
00:09:03.900 --> 00:09:05.360
[HIGUMA]
Again, huh?

232
00:09:05.690 --> 00:09:06.360
Fine!

233
00:09:06.360 --> 00:09:06.900
Hm?!

234
00:09:06.900 --> 00:09:08.110
[LUFFY]
Ahh!

235
00:09:08.110 --> 00:09:11.280
I don't think I said anything
to offend you personally.

236
00:09:11.280 --> 00:09:13.660
You think wrong! Now apologize!

237
00:09:14.030 --> 00:09:15.200
Get your foot off me!

238
00:09:15.200 --> 00:09:17.370
Let the boy go, I beg you!

239
00:09:17.660 --> 00:09:18.450
[HIGUMA]
Huh?

240
00:09:18.450 --> 00:09:21.960
[MAYOR WOOP SLAP]
He's a child! I don't intend to fight you,

241
00:09:21.960 --> 00:09:24.090
and I'll even pay you to stop this.

242
00:09:24.090 --> 00:09:27.300
Just let him live! That's all I ask!

243
00:09:27.300 --> 00:09:29.260
Ah, a senior citizen.

244
00:09:29.260 --> 00:09:31.470
Leave it to you to be reasonable.

245
00:09:31.470 --> 00:09:32.890
[gasps]

246
00:09:32.890 --> 00:09:33.930
[HIGUMA]
But you're outta luck.

247
00:09:33.930 --> 00:09:34.720
[gasps]

248
00:09:34.720 --> 00:09:36.810
The brat's already made me angry,

249
00:09:36.810 --> 00:09:39.520
so not even your pitiful prayers
can save him now.

250
00:09:39.520 --> 00:09:40.640
[MAYOR WOOP SLAP]
Please, no!

251
00:09:40.640 --> 00:09:43.270
That rubber face of yours was
real entertaining for a sec,

252
00:09:43.270 --> 00:09:45.560
but now all I want to do is bash it in.

253
00:09:45.560 --> 00:09:49.320
You guys don't fight fair!
You're scum! Lemme go!

254
00:09:51.110 --> 00:09:54.200
[HIGUMA]
Forget selling him. Let's just kill him!

255
00:09:55.160 --> 00:09:55.910
[MAKINO]
Luffy!

256
00:09:55.910 --> 00:09:57.700
Have mercy on him, sir!

257
00:09:57.700 --> 00:09:59.200
[BANDITS chuckling]

258
00:10:01.080 --> 00:10:03.540
[SHANKS]
Nobody was at the port to greet us.

259
00:10:03.540 --> 00:10:05.670
[MAKINO, MAYOR WOOP SLAP gasp]

260
00:10:05.670 --> 00:10:07.500
I figured something must be wrong.

261
00:10:07.500 --> 00:10:08.710
[MAKINO, MAYOR WOOP SLAP gasp]

262
00:10:08.710 --> 00:10:10.710
The mountain bandits again?

263
00:10:10.710 --> 00:10:11.920
Captain, you're here!

264
00:10:11.920 --> 00:10:13.010
Hey, Luffy.

265
00:10:13.010 --> 00:10:14.760
Didn't you say before that your punches

266
00:10:14.760 --> 00:10:16.800
were as deadly as getting shot with a pistol?

267
00:10:17.300 --> 00:10:18.760
[grunts] Shut up, okay?

268
00:10:18.760 --> 00:10:21.390
You're still in town? Shove off, already.

269
00:10:22.890 --> 00:10:23.480
[MAKINO gasps]

270
00:10:24.190 --> 00:10:26.400
[HIGUMA]
You'd best leave before you get hurt.

271
00:10:26.400 --> 00:10:30.110
Take one step closer and my friend
here's gonna blow your head clean off.

272
00:10:30.110 --> 00:10:31.530
[LUFFY grunts]

273
00:10:31.940 --> 00:10:34.070
Didn't you hear what the man said?

274
00:10:34.070 --> 00:10:35.950
Do you feel like dying today, buddy?

275
00:10:35.950 --> 00:10:37.910
[BANDITS laughing]

276
00:10:37.910 --> 00:10:40.290
Well, now that you've drawn your pistol,

277
00:10:40.290 --> 00:10:41.910
do you plan to actually use it?

278
00:10:41.910 --> 00:10:43.620
What? I'm holdin' it, ain't I?

279
00:10:43.620 --> 00:10:46.290
What I'm trying to tell you is that
guns aren't for making threats.

280
00:10:46.290 --> 00:10:47.840
They're made for actions.

281
00:10:55.680 --> 00:10:57.010
[BANDITS gasp]

282
00:10:58.760 --> 00:11:00.260
No way, I don't believe it!

283
00:11:00.260 --> 00:11:02.140
Yeah, these bastards fight dirty!

284
00:11:02.140 --> 00:11:03.430
A little.

285
00:11:03.430 --> 00:11:05.310
Oh, were you expecting saints?

286
00:11:05.310 --> 00:11:08.310
Who the hell do you think
you're dealing with here?

287
00:11:08.310 --> 00:11:09.820
In case it wasn't obvious,

288
00:11:09.820 --> 00:11:12.070
you fellas have picked a fight
with a crew of pirates.

289
00:11:12.070 --> 00:11:13.190
Shut your trap!

290
00:11:13.190 --> 00:11:15.530
This ain't about you,
so take your crew and go!

291
00:11:15.910 --> 00:11:17.280
[SHANKS]
Listen up, bandits.

292
00:11:17.280 --> 00:11:21.490
If I'm sprayed with alcohol or doused
with food, hell, even if I'm spit on,

293
00:11:21.490 --> 00:11:24.250
most of the time I'll laugh it off and forget it.

294
00:11:24.250 --> 00:11:25.870
But...

295
00:11:26.330 --> 00:11:29.080
Regardless of what
your reasoning may be,

296
00:11:29.080 --> 00:11:33.380
if you hurt a friend of mine,
you can believe you're gonna pay for it.

297
00:11:33.380 --> 00:11:35.930
[gasps] Is he for real?

298
00:11:35.930 --> 00:11:38.760
[laughs] Oh, we are, are we?

299
00:11:38.340 --> 00:11:41.890
[exciting music]

300
00:11:38.760 --> 00:11:41.890
Go on, fellas! Show these
wimps a thing or two!

301
00:11:41.890 --> 00:11:46.640
[BANDITS yelling]

302
00:11:46.640 --> 00:11:48.940
[BECKMAN]
I'll handle this. Should be easy.

303
00:11:50.270 --> 00:11:52.980
[yelling]

304
00:11:52.980 --> 00:11:54.150
[yelps]

305
00:11:54.150 --> 00:11:56.110
[BANDITS yelling]

306
00:11:56.110 --> 00:11:56.650
[BECKMAN grunts]

307
00:11:56.650 --> 00:11:57.530
[sounds of clashing]

308
00:11:57.530 --> 00:11:59.240
[BANDITS scream]

309
00:12:01.410 --> 00:12:04.330
Don't get too cocky. Stay focused.

310
00:12:05.370 --> 00:12:09.210
If you wanted to fight us, you should've
brought a warship or something bigger.

311
00:12:10.130 --> 00:12:11.540
This is so cool.

312
00:12:12.420 --> 00:12:13.460
Amazing.

313
00:12:13.460 --> 00:12:14.880
[gasps] No, hold on!

314
00:12:14.880 --> 00:12:17.170
The kid was the one who
attacked us first, all right?

315
00:12:17.170 --> 00:12:19.550
Either way, you're still
a wanted man, aren't ya?

316
00:12:19.550 --> 00:12:20.680
[gasps]

317
00:12:22.260 --> 00:12:23.220
[ROUX]
A smokescreen!

318
00:12:23.220 --> 00:12:26.020
[LUFFY] Stop it! Let me go already!

319
00:12:23.810 --> 00:12:25.100
[HIGUMA] Come with me!

320
00:12:28.310 --> 00:12:29.020
[SHANKS]
Luffy!

321
00:12:29.020 --> 00:12:31.020
Oh, crap, I let the bandit take him!

322
00:12:31.020 --> 00:12:32.690
What are we gonna do?!

323
00:12:31.690 --> 00:12:34.020
Calm down, Boss! There's
no use freakin' out over it!

324
00:12:34.530 --> 00:12:36.570
We'll find him in no time, I swear!

325
00:12:36.570 --> 00:12:39.360
Oh boy. Can't believe this guy.

326
00:12:39.910 --> 00:12:43.200
[HIGUMA laughs]
Guess I made a clean getaway!

327
00:12:43.700 --> 00:12:46.160
Sorry, got no need for you anymore.

328
00:12:46.160 --> 00:12:47.660
[LUFFY grunting]

329
00:12:48.540 --> 00:12:50.040
Ha! See ya, runt!

330
00:12:50.040 --> 00:12:52.670
[LUFFY yelps]
Dammit! I suck!

331
00:12:52.670 --> 00:12:56.710
These guys are worthless bandits,
but I still couldn't get one hit in!

332
00:12:56.710 --> 00:12:59.800
I hate this! It's not fair!

333
00:12:59.800 --> 00:13:03.760
[HIGUMA laughing]
Guys, did you see the looks on their faces?

334
00:13:03.760 --> 00:13:07.060
All pirates are nothing but
cowards and weaklings.

335
00:13:07.060 --> 00:13:08.390
[LUFFY]
Shut up!

336
00:13:08.390 --> 00:13:09.940
Don't make fun of
them like that!

337
00:13:09.940 --> 00:13:10.940
[MAKINO]
Luffy, no!

338
00:13:11.810 --> 00:13:12.400
[HIGUMA]
Huh?

339
00:13:12.400 --> 00:13:15.820
[LUFFY]
Take back what you said
about Shanks and his crew!

340
00:13:18.990 --> 00:13:20.280
[HIGUMA laughing]

341
00:13:20.280 --> 00:13:22.450
[gurgling]

342
00:13:22.450 --> 00:13:24.700
Ha. Stupid brat.

343
00:13:27.580 --> 00:13:29.870
[menacing orchestral music]

344
00:13:29.870 --> 00:13:31.580
[gasps] What the hell?!

345
00:13:31.920 --> 00:13:32.620
[screams]

346
00:13:34.170 --> 00:13:35.840
[gurgling] Help me!

347
00:13:35.840 --> 00:13:37.800
[LORD OF THE COAST growls]

348
00:13:39.510 --> 00:13:40.760
[LUFFY]
Here it comes!

349
00:13:42.180 --> 00:13:43.180
Oh no!

350
00:13:43.180 --> 00:13:46.100
[LUFFY's gurgling continues]

351
00:13:46.100 --> 00:13:47.510
[LORD OF THE COAST yowls]

352
00:13:47.510 --> 00:13:50.140
[LUFFY screaming]

353
00:13:57.440 --> 00:13:59.150
Shanks, you found me!

354
00:14:06.450 --> 00:14:07.990
[SHANKS]
Get lost.

355
00:14:08.660 --> 00:14:13.290
[LORD OF THE COAST whimpering]

356
00:14:28.220 --> 00:14:30.770
[LUFFY sobbing quietly]

357
00:14:30.060 --> 00:14:32.680
[contemplative music]

358
00:14:30.770 --> 00:14:32.680
[SHANKS]
I'm in your debt, Luffy.

359
00:14:32.680 --> 00:14:35.230
Makino told me about
how you stood up for us,

360
00:14:35.230 --> 00:14:37.560
how you were willing to fight
and put yourself on the line.

361
00:14:39.980 --> 00:14:41.900
Hold on, you can't cry.

362
00:14:41.900 --> 00:14:43.110
You're a man now.

363
00:14:44.530 --> 00:14:47.120
I know, but this is bad!

364
00:14:48.330 --> 00:14:50.490
You lost your arm!

365
00:14:53.160 --> 00:14:56.080
Oh, no need to worry about that.
I've got another one.

366
00:14:57.210 --> 00:14:59.000
I'm just glad you're safe.

367
00:15:01.800 --> 00:15:08.720
[LUFFY wailing]

368
00:15:08.720 --> 00:15:11.680
[NARRATOR]
Luffy learned many important things that day:

369
00:15:11.680 --> 00:15:15.270
the harshness of the sea,
his own powerlessness,

370
00:15:15.270 --> 00:15:16.940
and most importantly,

371
00:15:16.940 --> 00:15:20.230
the greatness of the man called Shanks.

372
00:15:20.230 --> 00:15:23.440
That's when young Luffy
resolved with all his heart

373
00:15:23.440 --> 00:15:25.610
he would become like him.

374
00:15:27.360 --> 00:15:28.530
[LUFFY]
Shanks.

375
00:15:28.530 --> 00:15:30.620
Are you really about to leave
the village for good?

376
00:15:30.620 --> 00:15:33.540
[SHANKS]
Uh-huh. Yep, it's time for us to part ways.

377
00:15:33.540 --> 00:15:34.960
I bet you'll miss me, wontcha?

378
00:15:35.710 --> 00:15:36.620
Yeah.

379
00:15:36.620 --> 00:15:38.920
But I'm not gonna beg to come with you,

380
00:15:38.920 --> 00:15:42.130
'cause I'm gonna become
a pirate all on my own!

381
00:15:42.130 --> 00:15:44.470
That's good, because I wouldn't
bring you with me anyways.

382
00:15:45.130 --> 00:15:47.720
I mean you'll never make it as a pirate, kiddo!

383
00:15:47.720 --> 00:15:49.850
Will, too! Just wait and see!

384
00:15:49.850 --> 00:15:52.890
I'll round up a crew that's
every bit as good as yours,

385
00:15:52.890 --> 00:15:55.060
and we'll find the world's greatest treasure.

386
00:15:55.770 --> 00:15:58.400
And I'm gonna be King of the Pirates!

387
00:15:59.310 --> 00:16:00.230
Oh?

388
00:16:00.810 --> 00:16:03.070
Planning to outdo me, are ya?

389
00:16:04.860 --> 00:16:05.990
Okay.

390
00:16:07.630 --> 00:16:08.450
Uh...

391
00:16:09.490 --> 00:16:12.330
If that's the case, I'll leave this here.

392
00:16:18.500 --> 00:16:23.800
[sobbing]

393
00:16:18.920 --> 00:16:21.170
[SHANKS]
It means more to me than anything.

394
00:16:24.380 --> 00:16:26.050
Give it back someday.

395
00:16:26.590 --> 00:16:28.760
After you become a great pirate.

396
00:16:29.130 --> 00:16:30.590
Okay...

397
00:16:31.470 --> 00:16:33.640
He really does have potential.

398
00:16:33.640 --> 00:16:34.640
I know.

399
00:16:34.640 --> 00:16:37.560
He reminds me of myself
back when I was a kid.

400
00:16:38.690 --> 00:16:40.060
[SHANKS]
Set sail!

401
00:16:42.110 --> 00:16:43.860
[NARRATOR]
One decade later,

402
00:16:43.860 --> 00:16:48.150
Luffy's own pirate adventure
began at the very same port.

403
00:16:49.610 --> 00:16:52.700
Ten Years Later

404
00:16:52.700 --> 00:16:55.370
I can't believe Luffy's finally leaving.

405
00:16:55.370 --> 00:16:58.910
Becoming a pirate is a great
dishonor to our village.

406
00:16:59.670 --> 00:17:02.500
[LUFFY sighs]
Couldn't ask for a better day for this!

407
00:17:02.960 --> 00:17:04.340
[LUFFY laughs]

408
00:17:08.470 --> 00:17:10.050
[LUFFY gasps]

409
00:17:11.340 --> 00:17:13.390
Hey, it's this big guy again.

410
00:17:13.390 --> 00:17:15.100
You shouldn't've done that.

411
00:17:15.100 --> 00:17:17.980
'Cause I've been training a lot
over the past ten years.

412
00:17:20.190 --> 00:17:21.230
[roaring]

413
00:17:21.650 --> 00:17:23.270
Gum-Gum...

414
00:17:25.230 --> 00:17:27.190
[LUFFY]
Pistol!

415
00:17:34.700 --> 00:17:35.580
[chuckles]

416
00:17:36.870 --> 00:17:39.620
That oughta teach ya, ya stupid fish!

417
00:17:46.170 --> 00:17:48.420
It's time to get goin'!

418
00:17:48.420 --> 00:17:51.220
I'm setting out to become

419
00:17:51.220 --> 00:17:53.800
King of the Pirates!
